Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:05.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Every night, your computer\Nis sitting there doing nothing.\NIt could be making you money.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.20,0:00:13.20,Default,,0,0,0,,You know how torrents work — \Nmillions of small computers, together, \Nmore powerful than any big server.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.20,0:00:21.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Now imagine the same thing, but for AI. \NThat's real. That exists.\N And your computer can be part of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.45,0:00:31.20,Default,,0,0,0,,But unlike torrents, this is completely legal. \NHere's why: companies need AI to get work done. \NBig cloud AI is expensive.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.20,0:00:40.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Your computer, combined with thousands of others,\N creates a cheap alternative. Companies are happy to pay for it. \NThat money goes to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.45,0:00:50.45,Default,,0,0,0,,There are other ways to earn from your computer. \NCrypto mining. GPU rental. Bandwidth sharing. \NThey all run your hardware at full blast, 24/7.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.45,0:00:59.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Your electricity bill goes up. Your computer sounds like\N a vacuum cleaner. Strangers run their code on your machine. \NAnd after all that — you earn pennies.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.95,0:01:08.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Or maybe you've heard about AI agents\N that trade stocks or run a business for you while you sleep. \NIn reality, most people lose money.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.95,0:01:20.70,Default,,0,0,0,,API costs run into thousands. The AI marks broken work as done. \NAnd when it makes a mistake — legally, that's on you. \NNot passive. Not safe.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.70,0:01:28.20,Default,,0,0,0,,We don't do any of that. \NYour computer runs a small, free AI \Nthat answers text questions. Light work. Low power.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.20,0:01:35.45,Default,,0,0,0,,No strangers' code. No money at risk. \NReal companies pay for real work. \NThat money goes to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.45,0:01:46.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Imagine you're playing chess alone. \NYou need to find the best move. \NYou sit there, thinking through every possibility —\N pawns, knights, bishops, rooks, queen.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.70,0:01:52.95,Default,,0,0,0,,One brain, so many options. \NYou can only think about so many moves\N before your time runs out.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.95,0:02:03.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Now imagine you have six helpers. \NYou give each one a piece type.\N You take pawns, you take knights, you take bishops.\N Each helper goes to a separate room.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.95,0:02:10.95,Default,,0,0,0,,They all think at the same time. \NTogether, they explore far more possibilities\N than you ever could alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.95,0:02:23.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Each one comes back with his best move. \NYou pick the winner. Next turn? \NYou show them all the new board, and they do it again. \NEvery turn, six brains. Every turn, a better move.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.20,0:02:33.20,Default,,0,0,0,,This works for any business problem. \NAnalyze two hundred customer reviews? \NSplit them across fifty computers. \NWrite fifty product descriptions?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.20,0:02:42.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Give each computer a different starting angle\N — formal, playful, technical — \Nthey all write at the same time. \NAnd it scales effortlessly.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.95,0:02:53.45,Default,,0,0,0,,If your computer can play games, it can do this. \NYou install a free local AI — it's not an agent, \Nit doesn't take over your computer, it doesn't go online.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.45,0:03:04.95,Default,,0,0,0,,You ask it a text question, it gives back a text answer.\N That's all it does. Our program is open-source — \Nyou can read every line of code and see it's legit.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.95,0:03:09.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Install both, click start, walk away. Seventeen minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.95,0:03:19.95,Default,,0,0,0,,When a customer pays for a job — \N65% goes to the workers. That's you. \N30% goes to the manager \Nwho split and combined the work.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.95,0:03:32.70,Default,,0,0,0,,And the platform — \Nthe website that connects everyone? Only 5%. \NFor comparison, Uber takes 25%. Apple takes 30%. \NThe platform takes 5.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.70,0:03:45.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Start as a worker tonight — \Nyour laptop earns while you sleep. \NLearn the system, become a manager — \Nthe same software, bigger earnings, \N30% of every job all to yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.45,0:03:56.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Go even bigger — download the code, \Nrun your own marketplace, \Ntake 5% of every transaction. \NSame technology. Three levels. \NYou choose how high you climb.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.95,0:04:05.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Every marketplace runs on the same \Nfree, open-source code. \NDon't trust one? Switch to another. \NOr download the code and start your own.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.70,0:04:13.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Competition keeps every marketplace honest. \NNobody can overcharge you — \Nbecause anyone can compete with them tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.70,0:04:22.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Sofia runs a small marketing agency. \NA client needs two hundred customer reviews \Nanalyzed by Friday. \NShe can't afford enterprise AI,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.70,0:04:30.45,Default,,0,0,0,,and she doesn't have time to read them herself. \NShe goes to a marketplace, submits the job, \Nsets her budget, and clicks submit.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.45,0:04:36.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Jade is a college student. \NShe installed the software \Non her gaming laptop last week —\N seventeen minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.95,0:04:45.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Tonight, while she sleeps, \Nher laptop picks up task number forty-seven \Nfrom Sofia's job and gets to work.\N Jade doesn't even know.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.20,0:04:52.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Marcus is a programmer by day. \NOn the side, he rents a cloud server \Nfor a few dollars a month \Nand runs our software on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.70,0:05:01.20,Default,,0,0,0,,When Sofia's job arrives, \Nhis server splits it into small tasks, \Nand sends one to each worker — \Nincluding Jade's laptop.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.20,0:05:08.70,Default,,0,0,0,,When all the workers finish, \NMarcus's server collects the answers \Nand combines them into one polished report.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.70,0:05:12.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Marcus didn't lift a finger. \NHis cloud server did everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.45,0:05:21.20,Default,,0,0,0,,And that website where Sofia submitted her job? \NAlex built it. \NHe downloaded the free open-source code, \Nset it up on his own domain,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.20,0:05:30.70,Default,,0,0,0,,and opened a marketplace. \NEvery transaction that flows through his platform, \Nhe earns 5%. \NThe marketplace runs itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.70,0:05:35.45,Default,,0,0,0,,That report saved my client's product launch. They just signed a year-long contract.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.45,0:05:40.45,Default,,0,0,0,,My laptop paid for my textbooks this semester. I didn't do anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.45,0:05:46.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Last month, my hive earned me more than my side of the rent. My roommate thinks I'm a genius.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.20,0:05:53.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Alex started with free code \Nand a ten-dollar domain name.\N His marketplace now handles \Nthousands of jobs a week.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.20,0:05:58.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Five percent of every transaction. \NHe's building the next eBay — of AI.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.45,0:06:03.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Your computer is going to sit idle again tonight. \NOr it could start working for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.20,0:06:09.45,Default,,0,0,0,,The software is free. \NThe setup takes seventeen minutes.\N Which step of the ladder will you reach?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.45,0:06:14.70,Default,,0,0,0,,This technology can also\N get you promoted at work —
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.70,0:06:24.70,Default,,0,0,0,,by saving your company a fortune. \NCheck out our Private Mode video.
